<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key G, 4/4. Bright march-like feel. LH "33" root position, RH fifths and thirds.
- A7 (secondary dominant) substituted as ⑥7 label. C#°7 → D7.
- Bridge (bars 9-12) uses A7→D9 color; tension builds to final verse.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH bass rises G→A→D at bars 9-10 bridge; contrary motion to descending melody.
- RH G5 climax at bar 1 beat 1; steps down through bridge.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Full bars 1-4; sustained bars 5-8 (sustain on repeats); climactic bridge 9-12; resolving close 13-16.
-->
